### XLVI. HOW A MAN WHO CURES HIMSELF BY AN ORACLE.

<span id="img_11500"></span> ![](img/11500.jpg)

When they would symbolize *a man who cures himself by an oracle*, they
delineate a WOOD PIGEON CARRYING A BRANCH OF LAUREL; for this bird when
sick deposits a branch of laurel in its nest, and recovers.

